Implemented retention trimming in the shared engine lifecycle:
- append-triggered retention after segment roll
- recovery-triggered retention during shared-engine maintenance
- trimming only applies to oldest rolled segments; the active segment is never rewritten or partially trimmed

Focused proof:
- `cargo test -p transit-core retention`

Observed result:
- size retention can drop fully rolled history while preserving the current active segment
- age retention can drop aged rolled segments on the next append lifecycle
